Drivers are being warned to expect severe delays after the A102 was closed Northbound on Blackwall Lane. Traffic is at a standstill on the approach to the tunnel. Tailbacks strech to the Woolwich Road flyover.  A diversion has been put in place but drivers have been urged to avoid the area. Met Police said they were alerted to the broken down vehicle after a collision at 11.02am. No injuries have been reported.